    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`nvim_buf_call()` on a hidden buffer leaks the internal autocmd-window restriction as `E813: Cannot close autocmd window` when the callback deletes/wipes the current buffer.\n\nThis seems related to vim/vim#9985 but the Neovim case is *distinct* because `nvim_buf_call()` is, well, Neovim. This API call reasonably looks like \"run with this buffer current\" helper, not `:doautoall`/autocommand-window entrypoint.\n\nThe problem is that hidden buffers it still goes through the `aucmd_prepbuf()`/`aucmd_win` - I think a neovim-only fix here is realistic.\n\nFound while (attempting to) resolve another issue - open to work on this.\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Save and source this script:\n```lua\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\nvim.api.nvim_buf_call(buf, function()\n vim.cmd.bwipeout({ bang = true })\nend)\n```\n\nand see:\n\n```\nError in <file>:\nE5113: Lua chunk: <file>:2: Lua: <file>:3: Vim:E813: Cannot close autocmd window\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'bwipeout'\n        <file>:3: in function <<file>.lua:2>\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_call'\n        <file>:2: in main chunk\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_call'\n        <file>:2: in main chunk\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither:\n\n1. `nvim_buf_call()` should handle this case without leaking the autocmd-window restriction\n2. it should fail with a clearer API-level error/documented restriction instead of `E813`\n\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.18.21\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix package registry",
